HEADWORD: Protoplasta
<hw>Pro`to*plas"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of fresh-water
rhizopods including those that have a soft body and delicate branched
pseudopodia. The genus <gen>Gromia</gen> is one of the
best-known.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protoplastic</ent>⟦br⟧
